name: United States Federal
description: US federal regulatory jurisdiction. SEC reporting (Exchange Act), FTC Act, CFIUS, ECPA, CLOUD Act, OFAC sanctions, export controls (EAR).

name: European Union
description: Supranational jurisdiction. GDPR (Reg 2016/679) max penalty 4% global turnover or EUR 20M. NIS2 Directive (2022/2555). Digital Services Act. EU AI Act. EU-US Data Privacy Framework (Jul 2023). com/compliance.

name: United Kingdom
description: UK GDPR + Data Protection Act 2018. ICO enforcement. Max penalty GBP 17.5M or 4% global turnover. UK-US Data Bridge (Oct 2023). National Security and Investment Act 2021.

name: Germany
description: Federal Data Protection Act (BDSG) supplements GDPR. BaFin oversight for financial-sector outsourcing (MaRisk/BAIT). BSI Act for critical infrastructure. State-level DPA (LfDI) enforcement.

name: Netherlands
description: GDPR enforced by Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens (Dutch DPA). Dutch Implementation Act GDPR (Uitvoeringswet AVG). Telecommunications Act for data center operators. nl.

name: Australia
description: Privacy Act 1988 + Australian Privacy Principles (APPs). OAIC enforcement. APRA CPS 234 for financial services. Notifiable Data Breaches scheme (Part IIIC). Critical Infrastructure Act 2018.

name: Singapore
description: PDPA (Personal Data Protection Act 2012). PDPC enforcement. MAS TRM guidelines for financial-sector customers. Cybersecurity Act 2018 for critical information infrastructure. gov.sg.

name: India
description: Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 (DPDP) enacted Aug 2023, rules pending. IT Act 2000 + SPDI Rules 2011 currently operative. RBI outsourcing guidelines for financial-sector customers.

name: United Arab Emirates
description: UAE PDPL (Federal Decree-Law No. 45/2021) effective Jan 2022. UAE Data Office enforcement. DIFC and ADGM have separate data protection regimes. UAE Cybercrime Law (Federal Decree-Law 34/2021).

name: Canada
description: PIPEDA governs private-sector data at federal level. Quebec Law 25 imposes additional requirements. OSFI B-10 guidelines for financial-sector outsourcing.

name: Mexico
description: Ley Federal de Proteccion de Datos Personales (LFPDPPP, 2010). INAI enforcement. Consent requirements for international transfers.

name: China
description: PIPL (effective Nov 2021) max penalty 5% annual revenue. Cybersecurity Law 2017 data localization for CIIO. Data Security Law 2021 data classification. CAC enforcement. Cross-border transfer security assessment required.

name: Switzerland
description: Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP/nDSG, revised Sep 2023). Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework. FINMA outsourcing circulars for financial-sector customers.

name: Malaysia
description: PDPA 2010 (Personal Data Protection Act) effective Nov 2013. JPDP under MCMC enforcement.

name: Egypt
description: Egypt Personal Data Protection Law No. 151/2020 (enacted Jul 2020, enforcement pending regulatory establishment).

name: Vietnam
description: Cybersecurity Law 2018 (Law 24/2018/QH14). Personal Data Protection Decree 13/2023/ND-CP (effective Jul 2023). Data localization requirements for certain categories.

name: Russia
description: Federal Law 152-FZ On Personal Data (2006, amended). Data localization requirement (Federal Law 242-FZ) mandates Russian citizen data on Russian servers.

name: Brazil
description: Lei Geral de Protecao de Dados (LGPD, Law 13.709/2018, effective Sep 2020). ANPD enforcement. Max penalty 2% revenue capped at BRL 50M per infraction.

name: Israel
description: Privacy Protection Law 5741-1981, Amendment 13 (effective 2024, aligned with GDPR). Privacy Protection Authority enforcement.

name: Japan
description: Act on Protection of Personal Information (APPI, amended Jun 2022). PPC enforcement. Max penalty JPY 100M for corporations. Japan-EU adequacy decision.

name: New Zealand
description: Privacy Act 2020. Office of the Privacy Commissioner enforcement. Mandatory breach notification. NZ-EU adequacy decision.

name: Hong Kong SAR
description: Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance (PDPO, Cap 486). Office of Privacy Commissioner enforcement. No data localization requirement. Cross-border transfers governed by DPP3.

name: State of Texas
description: Texas Data Privacy and Security Act (TDPSA, effective Jul 2024). Texas Identity Theft Enforcement and Protection Act. Texas Business Organizations Code. Franchise tax.

name: Commonwealth of Virginia
description: Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA, effective Jan 2023). Virginia Computer Crimes Act.

name: State of California
description: CCPA/CPRA (effective Jan 2023). California AG + CPPA enforcement. Max penalty $7,500 per intentional violation. Private right of action for data breaches.

name: State of Delaware
description: Delaware General Corporation Law (DGCL). Court of Chancery exclusive jurisdiction for corporate disputes. Franchise tax.

name: State of Illinois
description: Illinois Personal Information Protection Act. Biometric Information Privacy Act (BIPA) with private right of action.

name: State of Missouri
description: Missouri Merchandising Practices Act (data breach provisions).

name: State of New Jersey
description: New Jersey data breach notification law (N.J. Stat. 56:8-161 et seq.).

name: State of Washington
description: Washington My Health My Data Act (effective Mar 2024).

name: State of Oregon
description: Oregon Consumer Privacy Act (OCPA, effective Jul 2024).

name: State of Arizona
description: Arizona data breach notification statute (A.R.S. 18-552). No comprehensive privacy law as of 2024.

name: State of Tennessee
description: Tennessee Information Protection Act (TIPA, effective Jul 2025).

name: State of Pennsylvania
description: Pennsylvania Breach of Personal Information Notification Act (73 P.S. 2303). No comprehensive privacy law.

name: State of Wisconsin
description: Wisconsin data breach notification (Wis. Stat. 134.98). No comprehensive privacy law.

name: State of Massachusetts
description: Massachusetts data security regulations (201 CMR 17.00). Data breach notification (Mass. Gen. Laws Ch. 93H). 00.

name: State of Georgia
description: Georgia Personal Identity Protection Act (O.C.G.A. 10-1-910 et seq.).

name: England and Wales
description: Companies Act 2006 governs incorporation. English common law system for employment and contract law.

name: Ontario, Canada
description: PIPEDA applies (no substantially similar provincial privacy law). Ontario Securities Commission oversight. Employment Standards Act 2000.

name: Quebec, Canada
description: Law 25 (modernized Sep 2023) provides Quebec-specific privacy requirements exceeding PIPEDA. Commission d'acces a l'information du Quebec (CAI) enforcement.

name: Bavaria, Germany
description: BayLDA (Bayerisches Landesamt fur Datenschutzaufsicht) enforces GDPR for private sector.

name: Hesse, Germany
description: HBDI (Der Hessische Beauftragte fur Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit) enforces GDPR.

name: Hamburg, Germany
description: HmbBfDI (Hamburg Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information) enforces GDPR.

name: New South Wales, Australia
description: State Records Act 1998. Government Information (Public Access) Act 2009. Federal Privacy Act 1988 applies to private sector.

name: Victoria, Australia
description: Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014. Information Privacy Act 2000. Federal Privacy Act 1988 applies to private sector.

name: Haryana, India
description: DPDP Act 2023 applies at federal level. State IT/ITeS policies govern incentives and employment.

name: Telangana, India
description: DPDP Act 2023 applies at federal level. Telangana State Industrial Policy governs IT sector.

name: Karnataka, India
description: DPDP Act 2023 applies at federal level. Karnataka Shops and Commercial Establishments Act.

name: Selangor, Malaysia
description: PDPA 2010 applies at federal level.

name: North Holland, Netherlands
description: GDPR enforced by Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens at national level.

name: FedRAMP
description: Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program. FedRAMP Moderate JAB P-ATO. FISMA, DoD SRG IL2/IL4, DFARS, NIST 800-171. fedramp.gov, rackspace.com/compliance/fedramp.

name: HIPAA
description: Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act. Privacy Rule (45 CFR 164 Subpart E), Security Rule (45 CFR 164 Subpart C), HITECH Act 2009. Max penalty $1.5M per violation category per year. HHS OCR enforcement. com/compliance.

name: PCI-DSS
description: Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard. PCI DSS v4.0 (mandatory Mar 2025). Penalties $5K-$100K/month from card brands. com/compliance.

name: CMMC / DFARS
description: Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification + DFARS. CMMC 2.0 final rule effective Dec 2024 (32 CFR Part 170). DFARS 252.204-7012. NIST SP 800-171. False Claims Act exposure. 0 final rule.

name: ITAR
description: International Traffic in Arms Regulations (22 CFR 120-130). US-persons-only access requirement. Criminal penalties up to $1M and 20 years per violation. DDTC enforcement.

name: GDPR
description: EU General Data Protection Regulation (Reg 2016/679). Max penalty EUR 20M or 4% global annual turnover. DPO required. DPIAs for high-risk processing. SCCs/BCRs for international transfers.

name: NIS2 Directive
description: EU Network and Information Security Directive 2 (2022/2555). Mandatory incident reporting (24h early warning, 72h notification). Max penalty EUR 10M or 2% global turnover for essential entities.

name: UK GDPR
description: UK GDPR (retained EU law) + Data Protection Act 2018. ICO enforcement. Max penalty GBP 17.5M or 4% global turnover. UK IDTA or UK Addendum to EU SCCs for transfers.

name: ISO 27001
description: International information security management standard (ISO/IEC 27001). Three-year certification cycle with annual surveillance by BSI. com/compliance/iso.

name: SOC 1/2/3
description: AICPA Service Organization Controls. SOC 1 (SSAE 18), SOC 2 Type II, SOC 3. Covers security, availability, privacy, confidentiality, processing integrity. Annual audit. com/compliance.

name: FISMA
description: Federal Information Security Modernization Act. NIST 800-53 control baseline. Required for all federal information systems. Continuous monitoring requirement. com/compliance/fedramp.
